228c245.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTri7jO_cCenTt53WGje49rZBgejdDiEOjh1Q";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:474;s:6:"height";i:360;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/511228995176291883/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:69:{i:0;s:22:"Ive been brain washed.";i:1;s:45:"I am going to start backpacking with a chair.";i:2;s:118:"My gut says to just get the Chair Zero but everyone I talk to says the little legs sink into soft ground all the time.";i:3;s:87:"I noticed on Helinox website they have a similar looking chair called the Ground Chair.";i:4;s:48:"It is 5oz heavier but offers a more stable base.";i:5;s:60:"Helinox Chair One is 11 Chair Zero is 9 high off the ground.";i:6;s:76:"If youre a tall person you might be more comfortable with Helinox Chair One.";i:7;s:135:"Also Chair Zero is a bit tighter around the hips so if youre an oversize person you would feel more comfortable with Helinox Chair One.";i:8;s:54:"Both Helinox One and Helinox Zero are low back chairs.";i:9;s:69:"Firstsizes while in the carry bag and weights while in the carry bag.";i:10;s:55:"135 x 4 weighs in at 11 pounds and supports 265 pounds.";i:11;s:57:"135 x 525 weighs in at 22 pounds and supports 320 pounds.";i:12;s:74:"Helinox is advertising the Zero as being very similar to the One but at a.";i:13;s:187:"While its still lighter than just about every other camp chair on the market by pounds its not quite as light and doesnt pack down quite as small as Helinoxs featherweight Chair Zero 1lb.";i:14;s:36:"2oz but it does have its own tricks.";i:15;s:127:"Instead of relying on spindly legs it sits low to the ground thus the name on a sturdy square base that holds up to 265 pounds.";i:16;s:123:"Unfortunately the small feet of the Chair Zero will sink into soft ground more easily than larger less packable feet would.";i:17;s:79:"A hard mostly flat surface is necessary for the most relaxation to be achieved.";i:18;s:108:"The Zeros small feet can sink into soft ground so youll want to be picky about where you choose to place it.";i:19;s:163:"For those with challenges in sand mud Helinox also sells a ground sheet for most of their chairs heres the one for the Chair Zero so that it floats on sand or mud.";i:20;s:110:"The ground sheet I have for the Camp Chair is very effective though if youre backpacking - it does add weight.";i:21;s:38:"Very light easy to setup and put away.";i:22;s:93:"It does sit low to the ground so its harder to get out of compared to a regular height chair.";i:23;s:98:"That being said sitting low to the ground is great as you can stretch out your legs and lean back.";i:24;s:38:"I dont like the legs on the Chair One.";i:25;s:72:"Under these conditions a chair however minimal can be a great civilizer.";i:26;s:140:"The new generation of lightweight aluminum frame sling chairs fills this need elegantly and the Helinox Ground Chair is my pick of the pack.";i:27;s:115:"I traded in a lighter Helinox Chair Zero in for this one and I am happy with the weight-for-functionality tradeoff.";i:28;s:33:"GROUND CHAIRS Foam or Inflatable.";i:29;s:66:"Rest either directly on the ground or a few inches off the ground.";i:30;s:82:"They dont have legs making them lighter and more compact than the elevated chairs.";i:31;s:91:"They are close to the ground so you will pick up dirt pine needles and other forest litter.";i:32;s:33:"They fold flat and can double as.";i:33;s:29:"Helinox ground chair vs zero.";i:34;s:49:"December 28 2020 Leave a comment Leave a comment.";i:35;s:47:"Regular price tag is less than for Zero 100 vs.";i:36;s:125:"120 though on sale prices for both are about the same 80 20 for REI item and more for Helinox I got my for 80 from campsaver.";i:37;s:21:"Orange color is cool.";i:38;s:29:"Helinox ground chair vs zero.";i:39;s:74:"Posted by on Dec 29 2020 in Uncategorized on Dec 29 2020 in Uncategorized.";i:40;s:53:"The Best Backpacking Chair for Sitting on the Ground.";i:41;s:19:"Crazy Creek Hex 20.";i:42;s:11:"1 lb 59 oz.";i:43;s:208:"Car Camper Day Hiker Urban Hiker Wilderness Backpacker The Crazy Creek Hex 2 is a slight upgrade to this timeless design which you have no doubt seen at concerts parks campsites and even on backpacking trips.";i:44;s:119:"The Helinox Chair Zero is an ultralight foldable backpacking chair that will keep you a solid 11 inches off the ground.";i:45;s:133:"Stretch out your legs lean back and let that campfire warm you in the backcountry all for 17 ounces in a highly packable form factor.";i:46;s:55:"If youre set on the lightest foldable chair this is it.";i:47;s:44:"Helinox ground chair vs chair zero 28122020.";i:48;s:40:"I have a flex lite and HAD a chair zero.";i:49;s:60:"The chair zero was lighter but it made you sit more upright.";i:50;s:55:"I prefer the angle of the back rest for the flex light.";i:51;s:34:"It allowed for a slight back lean.";i:52;s:51:"Also if you get the flex lite do your self a favor.";i:53;s:55:"Go on Amazon an order the trekology chair ground sheet.";i:54;s:50:"Itll stop your chair from sinking into the ground.";i:55;s:182:"The main zero gravity chair vs recliner chair difference is the fact that while both chairs allow you to adjust the back reclining angle the zero gravity chair also raises your feet.";i:56;s:117:"After all in order to be in the zero gravity position you will need to be with your feet at least at the heart level.";i:57;s:35:"Helinox ground chair vs chair zero.";i:58;s:84:"Por Dic 28 2020 Uncategorized 0 Comentarios Dic 28 2020 Uncategorized 0 Comentarios.";i:59;s:126:"While the seat depth is the same as our popular Chair One the Zeros seat is slightly more narrow and sits lower to the ground.";i:60;s:108:"For people looking for a taller and wider profile we also offer a range of High-Back and Extra-Roomy chairs.";i:61;s:30:"Packed size is 35 x 10 x 10cm.";i:62;s:69:"Normally the seat angle is set to around 5-10 average is around a 15.";i:63;s:113:"Finally most of the aluminum structures are in a bending mode as there is a torque on the tubes Force X Distance.";i:64;s:86:"So imagine that such a chair can support up to 265 lb 120 kg this is quite remarkable.";i:65;s:51:"This is a lightweight and strong folding camp tool.";i:66;s:102:"Ground Chairs frame is built with ultra-lightweight and exceptionally strong DAC aluminum alloy poles.";i:67;s:154:"This advanced pole technology was developed for expedition-level backpacking tents and is trusted and relied on by the worlds most discerning adventurers.";i:68;s:68:"Helinox is the only furniture brand to use DAC aluminum alloy poles.";}}